versionCheck() - Method in class CommentConfiguration
Method to figure out if we are out of date or running on an older / newer build of Spout.
versionURL - Variable in class Configuration
Link to the location of the recent version number, the file should be a text with <version> x.y.rb-Bb for example your pom.yml
For a better explanation of the version number scheme please look here: Wiki
For those people who are interested what the version number means, e.g 3.5.1597-20
x.y.rb-Bb

x = Major Version = Major new stuff or internal rework
y = Minor Version = Minor new stuff and bug fixes
rb = Recommended Build of Spout
b = Development Build Version = if you have development builds for example B7
